{
  "stem": "24364.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- and I had actually a couple of friends from my hometown who had come with one of the other boats, so I was in a hut with one of them, which was really very nice.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, after about four or five days, we were told that the people who had been on the and the people who had not been on the like us, had to be separated.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I still think that had we known what was going to happen, which we didn't, we could have stayed in that hut and nobody would have said anything and we could have stayed in Palestine, but we were stupid.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, we were young.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They told us we had to go to a different hut, so we went.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And soon after that, they started to erect barbed wire between those two camps, the ones on one side and the other one on the other side.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On one side were the people who had been on the which were considered shipwrecked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And on the other side were people like me, who had not been on the yet and were not considered shipwrecked.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so it was decided to deport the people who had not been shipwrecked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so after two, three days on the other side of the camp, we were told that-- pack your things and tomorrow morning you're going to leave.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You're going to be transported or deported to Mauritius.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
